<h2>
  Configuration
</h2>

<p>
  There isn't any configuration needed. A basic stylesheet will be included, unless you opt out of it:
</p>

<CodeBlock @language="javascript" @code="// ember-cli-build.js
// ...
let app = new EmberApp({
  'ember-date-components': {
    'includeCSS': false
  }
});
// ..." />

<p>
  You are encouraged to overwrite the styles to fit your app.
  If you use Sass, you can also import a provided partial (don't forget to disable the CSS import in that case!).
  You'll also need to ensure that the ember-basic-dropdown partial is correctly imported. If you don't use Sass,
  it will automatically be added to your project (via the ember-basic-dropdown addon).
</p>

<CodeBlock @language="scss" @code='@import "ember-basic-dropdown";
@import \"ember-date-components/addon\";' />

<p>
  This partial uses a few variables that you can set:
</p>

<CodeBlock @language="scss" @code='$font-size: 16px !default;
$border-radius: 3px !default;
$date-picker-color-primary: #2ecc71 !default;
$date-picker-color-secondary: #ccc !default;
$date-picker-color-background: #eee !default;

@import "ember-date-components/addon";' />

<p>
  Note that if you use this partial, you set
  <CodeInline @language="javascript" @code="includeCSS: false" />
  .
</p>
